      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GALBA MAJOR (2) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Wentworth Park behind Ritza Tears (30.11) in a NG. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with two wins from two starts. Key chance in this line up. MASTER MCGRAW (3) has been out of the placings last two but shapes well for this if he can recapture his strong win a few runs back, getting around this track over 457m in 25.93. Has the ability and looks a key chance. FOREST PRINCE (4) has been out of the placings at his last couple but on the winners' heels when placing three back (23.18) in a Grade 4/5 at Dubbo. Solid beginner and with a good start can clear the tricky draw. Can find the frame this time. MAGIC I AM (6) is a surprise last-start placegetter who should be thereabouts.",
